The Beginning
Tom & Jason started Wealth Aspirations in December 2012 having worked as Independent Financial Advisers at various different companies. January the 1st 2013 was the day of the Retail Distribution Review; the day on which commission was finally scrapped from all investments and the day that required advisers to have a much higher level of knowledge. They decided that, as the industry was growing up and becoming more regulated and required more qualifications, it would be a great time to start Wealth Aspirations. A huge need was identified for independent advisers in light of the countless numbers of 'advisers' being laid off by the major banks alongside a growing market of people like you whom require sound financial advice.

Most financial advisers are excellent, but even the best can give ‘poor advice’ if they can only offer a narrow range of products.

I’m passionate about my profession so, after 20 years in the business, I decided to go it alone and set up my own firm. We are an authorised people focused financial services business that helps clients finance and protect property transactions. We have a duty of care to provide advice on the best mortgage or insurance product that matches your specific requirements and personal circumstances.

We use the acronym “KIST” to describe what you can expect from us.  

    Knowledgeable: You will find us up to speed on the latest products and the best providers;
    Integrity: You can rely on us to act ethically, morally and recommend the right solution;
    Service: You can expect an exceptional and personal service; and
    Trust: You can be sure we will treat everything you share with us in strict confidence.

We may be a fairly young business yet we have financed / written over £20m worth of mortgages and protection insurance in just over 2 years.

Who are you?

As a prospective homeowner looking to finance the purchase or someone looking to replace a an existing mortgage you are likely to be spoilt for choice. Choosing the right product and covering the risk can be challenging assuming your affordability (can you afford to service and repay the debit as well as live?) is acceptable to lenders.

We imagine you are like the vast majority of people we talk to though: fed up with ‘experts’ who use jargon and complex phrases that confuse.  We speak your language whether you are a first time buyer, a first time mover, an experienced property investor or someone about to build a buy to let portfolio.

Who are we?

We are people who are here when you need us not here when it suits us. We don’t work 9-5. We recognise that our clients are likely to be busy people who want to talk outside of office hours.

You will find us approachable, receptive, straight talking and above all, great listeners. After all if we are to get the best terms for you we need to understand you, your financial position and future aspirations.

We pride ourself on a personal and honest approach to advice that we give our clients. Plans varying from no monthly payments to ensuring that your loved ones receive an inheritance, we will tailor a plan to suit you. Most importantly if we discover equity release is not right for you we will tell you.
At Equity Release Associates, we offer comprehensive financial advice designed to protect and enhance your future prosperity.
